Biography
 Father, John Elroy McCaw, started a business acquiring several television and radio stations. He also founded Centralia, Washington's first radio station, KELA, and owned the Lewis and Clark Hotel. In 1969, John passed away; the family faced several lawsuits and debts that claimed most of John's estate. After repaying the company's accumulated debts and taxes, the family retained a small Centralia cable company. After his father's death, Craig McCaw took the helm of the cable company and set out to rebuild ...
