Interests, Passion, Hobbies

Kind of Interests, Passion and Hobbies: Politics
Description: Generous political donor gives primarily to Republican candidates and causes. Lifetime giving exceeds $1.2 million.


Kind of Interests, Passion and Hobbies: Outdoors - Fishing
Description: Holds a fishing license in Oregon.


Kind of Interests, Passion and Hobbies: Vehicles - Cars
Description: McCaw collects classic cars, and reportedly purchased a 1962 Ferrari 250 GTO in May 2012 for $35 million, one of the highest prices ever paid for a car at that time. He and his younger brother Bruce were at one time believed to own as many as 400 cars and to have spent well over $100 million on new acquisitions since the early 1990s. 

Contact us to see more Interests, Passion, Hobbies
Philanthropy

Giving Profile: President and Director of the Craig and Susan McCaw Foundation. In 2012, the foundation had assets exceeding $36 million and total giving exceeded $3 million. It gives primarily to education, social and human services, environmental causes. Recipients include:  Horatio Alger Association, Santa Barbara Cottage Hospital, Santa Barbara Youth Ensemble. In 2003, McCaw brothers donated $20 million to Seattle Opera. The opera named its new opera house in honor of their mother Marion. In May 2013, McCaw joined The Giving Pledge, a campaign founded by Bill Gates and Warren Buffett, which encourages the wealthiest people in the world to give most of their wealth to philanthropic causes. 

